; Signed comparisons on bitvec 1
; In 1-bit signed: value 1 represents -1, value 0 represents 0.
; So -1 < 0, meaning slt(1, 0) should be true.
1 sort bitvec 1
2 one 1
3 zero 1
; slt(1, 0): -1 < 0 is true
4 slt 1 2 3
5 not 1 4
6 bad 5
; sgt(0, 1): 0 > -1 is true
7 sgt 1 3 2
8 not 1 7
9 bad 8
; sgte(0, 1): 0 >= -1 is true
10 sgte 1 3 2
11 not 1 10
12 bad 11
